TopicTitle: Need help in solving a crash

Articles.Content: My KSP program has not been used since 1.2. So now I've come back to it and added my usual mods, and now the game continues to crash no matter what I do. I read the output of the crash file but can't seem to understand what is causing the game to crash. If any of you can help me with this it would be very appreciated! output log: Raw Pastebin
Did you confirm the mods were of the proper version for 1.2?

You log says you are using 1.3.0 which is odd because if you would use the beta branch you would actually have 1.3.1. And there are two outdated mods for 1.2. So there's two possibilities:

A: You use 1.3.0 in which case you have to be either extra conscious to not use mods for 1.3.1 (and 1.2) because any mod that adds a custom entry to the game's difficulty menu will be incompatible. Or you should upgrade to 1.3.1.

B: You are actually using the current version 1.4.3 and your log is old and outdated because the new engine stores the log in a different location: https://docs.unity3d.com/Manual/LogFiles.html

Well after some digging, I found the problem. My computer is having some issues with my current amount of RAM , so I bought another 8gb and replaced the 6gb that was there, and that seemed to work, somewhat. However, the game froze on some of the mods, im supposing that the model of the part is not loading correctly. So I completely deleted all of the mods and used CKAN to mod the game for me. I appreciate the help anyways!
